class UndergraduateStudentProfile {
private:
    std::string fullName;
    std::string studentID;
    double gpa;

public:
    UndergraduateStudentProfile(
        const std::string& name,
        const std::string& id,
        double academicGPA
    );

    void setFullName(const std::string& name);
    std::string getFullName() const;

    void setStudentID(const std::string& id);
    std::string getStudentID() const;

    void setGPA(double gpa);
    double getGPA() const;

    void displayProfile() const;
};
```

*Highlighted section: Constructor and Member Functions*

The constructor initializes the student's name, ID, and GPA. It ensures that the GPA is within a valid range (0.0 to 4.0). The member functions allow for setting and retrieving the student's details, providing encapsulation and data integrity.

```cpp
UndergraduateStudentProfile::UndergraduateStudentProfile(
    const std::string& name,
    const std::string& id,
    double academicGPA
) : fullName(name), studentID(id), gpa(academicGPA) {
    if (gpa < 0.0 || gpa > 4.0) {
        gpa = 0.0;
    }
}
```

*Highlighted section: Display Function Implementation*

The `displayProfile()` function is a utility that prints the student's details in a formatted manner, making it easy to view all information at once.

```cpp
void UndergraduateStudentProfile::displayProfile() const {
    std::cout << "Student Profile:" << std::endl;
    std::cout << "Full Name: " << fullName << std::endl;
    std::cout << "Student ID: " << studentID << std::endl;
    std::cout << "GPA: " << gpa << std::endl;
}
```

